    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "There seems to be some kind of rebinding loop - triggered by the fact that tailnet knows it doesn't have a usable UDP socket.\r\n\r\n```\r\n\"2023-09-18 11:06:44.982 [debu]  net.tailnet.net.wgengine: magicsock: last netcheck reported send error. Rebinding.\"\r\n\"2023-09-18 11:06:44.982 [debu]  net.tailnet.net.wgengine: magicsock: [warning] failed to force-set UDP read buffer size to 7340032: operation not permitted; using kernel default values (impacts throughput only)\"\r\n\"2023-09-18 11:06:44.982 [debu]  net.tailnet.net.wgengine: magicsock: [warning] failed to force-set UDP write buffer size to 7340032: operation not permitted; using kernel default values (impacts throughput only)\"\r\n\"2023-09-18 11:06:44.982 [debu]  net.tailnet.net.wgengine: magicsock: [warning] failed to force-set UDP read buffer size to 7340032: operation not permitted; using kernel default values (impacts throughput only)\"\r\n\"2023-09-18 11:06:44.983 [debu]  net.tailnet.net.wgengine: magicsock: [warning] failed to force-set UDP write buffer size to 7340032: operation not permitted; using kernel default values (impacts throughput only)\"\r\n\"2023-09-18 11:06:44.983 [debu]  net.tailnet.net.wgengine: Rebind; defIf=\\\"eth0\\\", ips=[192.168.100.148/24 fe80::5054:ff:fee8:4244/64]\"\r\n\"2023-09-18 11:06:44.983 [debu]  net.tailnet.net.wgengine: magicsock: closing connection to derp-999 (rebind-default-route-change), age 1s\"\r\n\"2023-09-18 11:06:44.983 [debu]  net.tailnet.net.wgengine: magicsock: 0 active derp conns\"\r\n\"2023-09-18 11:06:44.984 [debu]  net.tailnet.net.wgengine: magicsock: adding connection to derp-999 for home-keep-alive\"\r\n\"2023-09-18 11:06:44.984 [debu]  net.tailnet.net.wgengine: magicsock: 1 active derp conns: derp-999=cr0s,wr0s\"\r\n```\r\n\r\nBut also, it only triggers reconnecting to DERP if the DERP connection local address is not one of the interface addresses.  I can't help but wonder whether in tests we connect over the loopback or something.",
